    1	# Batch Mobius Sieve: Recursive Halving for phi(x,a)
    2	
    3	**Date:** 2026-04-05  
    4	**Verdict:** CLOSED -- exponential blowup makes this strictly worse than standard methods.
    5	
    6	## Idea
    7	
    8	Replace the standard Meissel-Lehmer recursion (remove one prime at a time) with recursive halving:
    9	
    10	```
    11	phi(x, a) = sum_{d | Q} mu(d) * phi(x/d, a/2)
    12	```
    13	
    14	where Q = product of the second-half primes {p_{a/2+1},...,p_a}. This reduces the recursion tree depth from pi(sqrt(x)) to O(log(pi(sqrt(x)))), but at the cost of exponential branching at each level (2^{half_size} squarefree divisors).
