    60	### Experiment 4: Roots of Unity
    61	
    62	P(omega^j) = 0 whenever any sieving prime p divides j*p modulo m. Since 2 is always a sieving prime, P(omega^j) = 0 whenever m | 2j. For small primes {2,3,5}, P is zero at most roots of unity for small m.
